robeger wrote:
&gt; On a different topic, will the 1.0.0 release support checkpointing?

To avoid destabilizing or delaying 1.0.0, checkpointing implementation has been
deferred. It&#39;s the first post-1.0.0 priority.

In the meantime, we&#39;ve slightly improved and better documented the recovery
journal feature, meaning that you can do a supplemental crawl after a crashed
crawl which, in terms of URI coverage, should pick up nearly where the crashed
crawl left off. (The crawls will still be logically separate, with different
running stats and a slight overlap near the crash time.)

- Gordon


